Analysis and Visualization

Log Odds ~ Correct Response

0-shot:

df_0s %>%
  group_by(correct) %>%
  summarise(mean_lp = mean(lp_ratio),
            sd_lp = sd(lp_ratio))
## # A tibble: 2 × 3
##   correct mean_lp sd_lp
##   <chr>     <dbl> <dbl>

## 2 yes        3.73  4.68
mod_full = lm(data = df_0s, lp_ratio ~ correct)
mod_reduced = lm(data = df_0s, lp_ratio ~ 1)

Accuracy ~ Prompting Method

Merging and aggregating data

df_merged = df_0s %>%
  bind_rows(df_1s) %>%
  mutate(few_shot = shots > 0) %>%
  mutate(few_shot = case_when(
    few_shot == TRUE ~ "Few-shot",
    few_shot == FALSE ~ "Zero-shot"
  )) 

## First show lp ratio
df_merged %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = few_shot, y = lp_ratio, fill = correct)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = 0) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "Prompting Method",
       fill = "Correct Response",
       y = "Log Odds (Yes vs. No)")

df_merged %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = few_shot, y = lp_ratio, fill = condition)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = 0) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "Prompting Method",
       fill = "Condition",
       y = "Log Odds (Yes vs. No)") +
  facet_wrap(~correct)

## Now calculate accuracy
df_merged = df_merged %>%
  mutate(accuracy = case_when(
    correct == "yes" & lp_ratio > 0 ~ 1,
    correct == "no" & lp_ratio < 0 ~ 1,
    correct == "yes" & lp_ratio < 0 ~ 0,
    correct == "no" & lp_ratio > 0 ~ 0
  ))

df_merged %>%
  group_by(few_shot) %>%
  summarise(accuracy = mean(accuracy))
## # A tibble: 2 × 2
##   few_shot  accuracy
##   <chr>        <dbl>
## 1 Few-shot     0.84 
## 2 Zero-shot    0.842
df_merged %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = few_shot,
             y = accuracy)) +
  stat_summary (fun = function(x){mean(x)},
                fun.min = function(x){mean(x) - 2*sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))},
                fun.max = function(x){mean(x) + 2*sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))},
                geom= 'pointrange', 
                position=position_dodge(width=0.95),
                size = .5, alpha = .5) +
  labs(x = "Prompting Method",
       y = "Accuracy") +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = .5, linetype = "dotted") +
  theme_minimal()

Accuracy is higher for “no” answers

df_scaling = read_csv("../../data/processed/all_models_comprehension_scaling_analysis.csv")

## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (5): model, sentence, answer, condition, correct
## dbl (4): shots, yes_lp, no_lp, lp_ratio

head(df_scaling)
## # A tibble: 6 × 9
##   model            sentence  answer shots condi…¹ correct yes_lp  no_lp lp_ratio
##   <chr>            <chr>     <chr>  <dbl> <chr>   <chr>    <dbl>  <dbl>    <dbl>
## 1 ada              A commit… Commi…     0 J       no       -1.88 -3.04   1.16e+0
## 2 babbage          A commit… Commi…     0 J       no       -2.90 -3.51   6.13e-1
## 3 curie            A commit… Commi…     0 J       no       -1.67 -1.67   9.14e-4
## 4 davinci          A commit… Commi…     0 J       no       -1.16 -1.82   6.57e-1
## 5 text-ada-001     A commit… Commi…     0 J       no       -2.54 -2.75   2.11e-1
## 6 text-babbage-001 A commit… Commi…     0 J       no       -2.64 -0.268 -2.38e+0
## # … with abbreviated variable name ¹​condition
## Now calculate accuracy
df_scaling = df_scaling %>%
  mutate(correct_response = case_when(
    correct == "yes" & lp_ratio > 0 ~ 1,
    correct == "no" & lp_ratio < 0 ~ 1,
    correct == "yes" & lp_ratio < 0 ~ 0,
    correct == "no" & lp_ratio > 0 ~ 0
  ))

df_scaling %>%
  group_by(model) %>%
  summarise(accuracy = mean(correct_response))
## # A tibble: 8 × 2
##   model            accuracy
##   <chr>               <dbl>
## 1 ada                 0.53 
## 2 babbage             0.518
## 3 curie               0.507
## 4 davinci             0.548
## 5 text-ada-001        0.525
## 6 text-babbage-001    0.47 
## 7 text-curie-001      0.47 
## 8 text-davinci-002    0.842
df_model_params = read_csv("../../data/processed/model_params.csv")
## Rows: 8 Columns: 3
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (2): Model, Model Type
## dbl (1): Parameters
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
df_model_params$model_stripped =c("ada", "babbage", "curie", "davinci",
                     "ada", "babbage", "curie", "davinci")

df_merged_scaling = df_scaling %>%
  mutate(Model = model) %>%
  left_join(df_model_params)
## Joining, by = "Model"
df_merged_scaling_summ = df_merged_scaling %>%
  mutate(Is_Joke = condition == "J") %>%
  group_by(model_stripped, Model, `Model Type`, Parameters, Is_Joke) %>%
  summarise(accuracy = mean(correct_response))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'model_stripped', 'Model', 'Model Type',
## 'Parameters'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
df_merged_scaling_summ %>%
  filter(Is_Joke == TRUE) %>%
  mutate(params_log = log10(Parameters)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Parameters,
             y = accuracy,
             shape = `Model Type`,
             color = model_stripped
             )) +
  geom_point(size = 6,
             alpha = .4) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = .85, ### Human accuracy 
              linetype = "dotted", color = "red",
             size = 1.2, alpha = .5) +
  geom_text_repel(aes(label=Model), size=3) +
  scale_x_log10() +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1)) +
  labs(x = "Parameters",
       y = "Accuracy",
       title = "Joke Comprehension Accuracy") +
  theme_minimal() +
  guides(color="none") +
  theme(text = element_text(size = 15),
        legend.position="bottom")

GPT-4 analysis

df_gpt4 = read_csv("../../data/processed/gpt4_comprehension.csv")
## Rows: 400 Columns: 6
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (6): response, word, answer, correct, response_lower, condition
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
table(df_gpt4$response)
## 
##  No Yes 
## 228 172
df_gpt4 = df_gpt4 %>%
  mutate(accurate = response_lower == correct) %>%
  mutate(Is_Joke = condition == "J")

df_gpt4_summ = df_gpt4 %>%
  group_by(Is_Joke) %>%
  summarise(accuracy = mean(accurate)) %>%
  mutate(model_stripped = "GPT-4",
         `Model Type` = "RLHF",
         Model = "GPT-4") %>%
  mutate(Parameters = 1700000000000)
  
df_merged_scaling_summ_with_gpt4 = df_merged_scaling_summ %>%
  bind_rows(df_gpt4_summ)

df_merged_scaling_summ_with_gpt4 %>%
  filter(Is_Joke == TRUE) %>%
  mutate(params_log = log10(Parameters)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Parameters,
             y = accuracy,
             shape = `Model Type`,
             color = model_stripped
             )) +
  geom_point(size = 6,
             alpha = .4) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = .85, ### Human accuracy 
              linetype = "dotted", color = "red",
             size = 1.2, alpha = .5) +
  geom_text_repel(aes(label=Model), size=3) +
  scale_x_log10() +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1)) +
  labs(x = "Parameters",
       y = "Accuracy",
       title = "Joke Comprehension Accuracy") +
  theme_minimal() +
  guides(color="none") +
  theme(text = element_text(size = 15),
        legend.position="bottom")
